OL,4,Cis on the side of workers
OL,6,FThe move is a "clear dividing line"
OL,7,Fbetween the Government and other
OL,8,Fpolitical parties such as Reform, he
OL,9,Fsaid.
OL,11,F"It is important that we get this over
OL,12,Fthe line despite those voices calling
OL,13,Ffor the provisions to be diluted," he
OL,14,Fsaid. "Tackling zero-hours contracts
OL,15,Fand giving rights from the first day
OL,16,Fin a job are popular with the public,
OL,17,Fincluding those who live in Clacton."
